<br>
Charms have random durations, which makes it very dangerous, even for enchanters who have a better spell setup to deal with it than mages. Root, slow, stun and mez makes all the difference.<br>
<br>
Mez, on the other hand, has a fixed duration and can be refreshed (keep a count and cast it just before it breaks to keep the mob freezed). With the new pet changes (pet not breaking mez) chain casting pets or healing and medding to finish the mob will now be easy. <br>
<br>
I think mez will be a very useful tool in soloing and grouping for mages. Charm will only be a toy since we are ill prepare to handle it when it breaks.<br>
<br>
-P.S.  Players can't have charmed pets and normal pets at the same time but NPCs can.<br>
<br>
